description.narrative:
This project aims to solve Georgia‘s Guria and Adjara regions‘ cardiological problems at the different levels of healthcare institutions. In order to share Lithuanian experience of healthcare achievements it will be trying to reach these objectives: 
•	to enhance an institutional ability to arrange more effective work of healthcare institutions;
•	to introduce the latest diagnostic and  treatment methods and algorithms;
•	to share a new healthcare delivery practice and improve the quality of services;
•	to appeal to experience of science specialists in order to rise the doctors’ qualification in Guria and Adjara regions using various forms, such as: internships, conferences, trainings and working visits.
The basic attention would be given to raise Guria and Adjara regions doctors’ qualification, to strengthen communication between healthcare institutions and cardiovascular diseases prevention. 
Raised qualification of the Georgia’s Guria and Adjara regions specialists’ will contribute for improving the quality in healthcare services. It would help to reduce mortality from heart and circulatory diseases, which are currently the main cause of deaths in Georgia.
